        <h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is GPTZero?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>GPTZero is an AI content detector founded in 2023 by Edward Tian. It analyzes text for signs of AI generation (low perplexity, low burstiness) and outputs a probability score that the content was written by a human or by an AI model like ChatGPT, Claude, or Gemini.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How much does GPTZero cost in 2026?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Free tier (10,000 words/mo), Premium $15/mo (150,000 words), Professional $25/mo (300,000 words), Enterprise custom. Annual billing saves about 20%.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How accurate is GPTZero?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>GPTZero claims 99% accuracy on its own benchmarks. Independent studies show real-world accuracy is closer to 80–85%, with false-positive rates of 4–8%. Accuracy drops to ~52% on heavily humanized AI output.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Does Google penalize AI content?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>No. Google's official position (March 2024 SearchLiaison statement) is that AI content is fine if it's helpful and high-quality. Google does penalize low-quality scaled content regardless of source. An AI detector tells you nothing about whether content will rank.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Is GPTZero worth it for SEO?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Not really. GPTZero is useful for educators, publishers, and HR teams who need to verify human authorship. For SEO professionals, it solves the wrong problem — Google ranks helpful content, not human-only content. Invest in research, optimization, and publishing instead.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">GPTZero vs Originality.ai — which is better?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Originality.ai has marginally better accuracy on freshly-generated GPT-4/5 content (91% vs 83% in our test). GPTZero has a more generous free tier and better classroom features. For SEO use specifically, neither tool moves the needle.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Can GPTZero detect humanized AI content?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Less reliably. Tools like Undetectable.ai, StealthGPT, and Quillbot's humanizer specifically rewrite AI output to defeat detectors. GPTZero catches around 50–60% of humanized content compared to 80–85% on raw AI output.</p></div></div>
          </div>
